---
title: One-Pot Chicken Sausage & Bean Soup with Kale & Carrot
description: The best kind of soup? One made in a single pot that boils up delicious flavor in just 20 minutes. This one does just that. Meaty Italian chicken sausage, kale, and carrot are cooked together, then rich chicken stock concentrate, cream sauce, and cannellini beans are stirred in for even more hearty flavor. We won’t judge if you lick the bowl clean...
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/620c1f0ed7058f2e91465903-b48ad27d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pot-chicken-sausage-bean-soup-620c1f0ed7058f2e91465903-0b9a26cf.pdf
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 690 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 66 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 17 g
  sodium: 2670 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-chicken-sausage-bean-soup-620c1f0ed7058f2e91465903
author: HelloFresh
time required: 20 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce. Trim @carrot{3%ounce}(peeled and sliced into half-moons) lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces. Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{13.4%ounce}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pot{} over medium heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce}; using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces, then add carrot, kale, and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sausage is cooked through, carrot is slightly softened, and kale begins to wilt, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> 1 tsp salt is used for 4 servings.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @cornstarch{1%tablespoon} with @water{1%TBSP} until mixture is smooth and no lumps remain.

> Mix with your finger to ensure there are no lumps!

Stir @chicken stock concentrate{2}, cornstarch slurry, half the beans, and @water{1 1/2%cups} into pot with sausage mixture. Using the back of a #wooden spoon{} or spatula, partially mash beans in pot.

Cover and bring to a boil, then immediately reduce to a low simmer. Cook until kale is wilted and broth has thickened slightly, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> Check if the kale is wilting evenly and stir occasionally if necessary.

Stir in @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, remaining beans, and a big squeeze of lemon juice. Cook until combined and warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Add another splash of water if you prefer a thinner broth.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.